---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How FreshLine Cleaning collects, uses and protects your personal information."
  slug="privacy-policy"
>
  <span class="last-updated">Last updated: May 2025</span>

  <h2>Who We Are</h2>
  <p>
    FreshLine Cleaning is a local carpet and upholstery cleaning service based in Birmingham,
    United Kingdom. We provide home cleaning services across Birmingham and the wider West Midlands.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you have any questions about this policy, please contact us at
    <a href="mailto:hello@example.com">hello@example.com</a> or call
    <a href="tel:+447000000000">+44 7000 000000</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>What Personal Data We Collect</h2>
  <p>We only collect the information we need to provide our service to you. This may include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Your name</strong> — so we know who we are speaking with</li>
    <li><strong>Phone number and/or email address</strong> — to reply to your enquiry and confirm your booking</li>
    <li><strong>Your address or postcode</strong> — to confirm we cover your area and to attend your appointment</li>
    <li><strong>Photos you send us</strong> — photos of carpets, sofas or other items sent to us for a quote via WhatsApp or email</li>
    <li><strong>Message content</strong> — the content of WhatsApp messages, emails or any other enquiries you send us</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We do not collect payment card details. Any payments are handled in cash or via bank transfer
    and are not processed through this website.
  </p>

  <h2>How We Collect Your Data</h2>
  <p>We collect data in the following ways:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>When you message us via WhatsApp</li>
    <li>When you call or text us</li>
    <li>When you send us an email</li>
    <li>When you use the contact form or click a contact button on our website</li>
    <li>When you share photos with us for a quote</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How We Use Your Data</h2>
  <p>We use the information you provide solely to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Respond to your enquiry and provide a quote</li>
    <li>Confirm and manage your booking</li>
    <li>Contact you about your appointment (e.g. reminders or rescheduling)</li>
    <li>Carry out the cleaning service at your address</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We will not use your data to send you unsolicited marketing messages without your permission.
    We will never sell your data to third parties.
  </p>

  <h2>Photos Sent for Quotes</h2>
  <p>
    Photos you send us via WhatsApp or email are used only to assess the job and provide you with
    an accurate quote. We may retain photos for a short period to reference during your appointment.
    We do not share your photos publicly or use them in any marketing without your explicit permission.
  </p>

  <h2>Analytics and Website Usage</h2>
  <p>
    Our website may use basic analytics tools (such as Google Analytics) to understand how visitors
    use the site. This may include information such as which pages are visited, how long visitors
    stay, and which device or browser they use. This data is anonymised and aggregated — it does
    not identify you personally.
  </p>
  <p>
    You can opt out of analytics tracking by adjusting your browser settings or using a browser
    extension such as the Google Analytics Opt-out Add-on. See our
    <a href="/cookies/">Cookie Policy</a> for more detail.
  </p>

  <h2>How Long We Keep Your Data</h2>
  <p>
    We keep your contact details and booking information for as long as is reasonably necessary to
    provide our service and for a short period afterwards in case of any follow-up questions or
    complaints. We do not retain data indefinitely, and we will delete your information when it is
    no longer needed.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you would like your data deleted sooner, please contact us and we will action your request
    promptly.
  </p>

  <h2>When We May Share Your Data</h2>
  <p>
    We do not share your personal data with third parties except in the following limited circumstances:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Where we are legally required to do so (for example, by a court order or regulatory obligation)</li>
    <li>Where it is necessary to protect the safety of any person</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We do not use third-party marketing platforms or share data with advertising networks.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Security</h2>
  <p>
    We take reasonable steps to keep your data secure. Enquiries and bookings are handled via
    WhatsApp (end-to-end encrypted), email, and phone. We do not store customer data on insecure
    systems or share login credentials.
  </p>
  <p>
    Please be aware that no method of communication over the internet is completely secure. If you
    have concerns about sharing sensitive information, please speak to us directly by phone.
  </p>

  <h2>Your Rights</h2>
  <p>Under UK data protection law (UK GDPR), you have the right to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Access</strong> — ask us what personal data we hold about you</li>
    <li><strong>Correction</strong> — ask us to correct inaccurate data</li>
    <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — ask us to delete your data</li>
    <li><strong>Restriction</strong> — ask us to stop processing your data in certain ways</li>
    <li><strong>Objection</strong> — object to how we use your data</li>
    <li><strong>Portability</strong> — ask for a copy of your data in a portable format</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the details below. We will respond
    within 30 days.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you are not satisfied with how we handle your data, you have the right to lodge a complaint
    with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at
    <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact Us About Privacy</h2>
  <p>For any privacy-related questions or requests, please contact us:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Email: <a href="mailto:hello@example.com">hello@example.com</a></li>
    <li>Phone: <a href="tel:+447000000000">+44 7000 000000</a></li>
    <li>Location: Birmingham, United Kingdom</li>
  </ul>
</LegalLayout>
